    • Method Detail

      • run

        public void run(Package[] types,
                int[] amountOfType)
        The primary method of the class GeneticAlgorithm. It creates an initial population of individuals with randomly generated chromosomes (that contain all of the packages specified). Then it uses a loop to evolve that population over several generations using the selection, crossover and mutation methods provided in the class.
        Parameters:
        types - An array containing all the types of packages that can be used to generate a solution.
        amountOfType - An array corresponding to the types array, designating the maximum number of packages that can be placed of the corresponding package type.

      • crossOver

        public Individual crossOver(Individual parent1,
                            Individual parent2)
        A method that applies a "modified crossover" which maintains package ordering and the correct number of each package type in the chromosome.
        Parameters:
        parent1 - The first parent.
        parent2 - The second parent.
        Returns:
        child The child created by crossover between the parents' chromosomes.
